# ============================================================================
# .dockerignore — keep the Fly build context small and never leak secrets
# ============================================================================
# `fly deploy` (and `docker build`) sends the entire build context to the
# Docker daemon / Fly remote builder before any COPY runs. Without this file
# we'd ship .git history, every node_modules, uploaded user PDFs, logs, the
# Cloudflare Worker bundle, and (worst of all) every .env file with prod
# secrets. This trims the context to just what infra/Dockerfile actually
# needs.
# ============================================================================

# --- VCS / IDE ----------------------------------------------------------------
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.github
.vscode
.idea

# --- Secrets — NEVER ship these ----------------------------------------------
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example
*.pem
*.key
demo-cookies.txt

# --- Dependencies (Dockerfile runs `npm ci` itself) ---------------------------
node_modules
**/node_modules
.pnpm-store
.turbo
**/.turbo

# --- Build outputs (rebuilt inside the image) --------------------------------
dist
**/dist
build
**/build
.next
**/.next
.open-next
**/.open-next
out
**/out
coverage
**/coverage
*.tsbuildinfo

# --- Runtime data the API generates locally — must not leak to the image ----
uploads
storage
apps/api/uploads
apps/api/storage
apps/api/logs
logs
**/logs

# --- Web app (the API image doesn't need its source) ------------------------
# pnpm `--frozen-lockfile` validates the lockfile against every workspace's
# package.json, so we re-include just the manifest (not src/, .next/, etc.)
# so the install step can verify @smart-apply/web's resolved tree without
# bringing 100+ MB of Next.js source into the API image.
apps/web
!apps/web/package.json
packages/shared/dist

# --- Docs / scripts that aren't needed at build time -------------------------
docs
README.md
ARCHITECTURE.md
CHANGELOG.md
QUICKSTART.md
**/*.md
# Re-include prompt templates — the LLM service loads these .md files at
# runtime (`/app/prompts/v1/skill-selector.md` etc.), so they MUST land in
# the image. Without this exception the container boots but blows up on the
# first generation request with `Template not found: v1/skill-selector.md`.
!apps/api/prompts/**/*.md
!apps/api/prisma/migrations/**/migration_lock.toml

# --- Tests / fixtures --------------------------------------------------------
# (tsconfig.build.json already excludes these from compilation; we just keep
# them out of the build context to shrink it. Exception: apps/api/test/ is
# COPYed by the Dockerfile, so we re-include it.)
**/*.spec.ts
**/*.test.ts
**/__tests__
**/__mocks__
test
**/test
!apps/api/test
!apps/api/test/**

# --- OS / editor cruft -------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# --- Misc ---------------------------------------------------------------------
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
.npm
.cache
